msgid "Determining Status and Reachability of Network Hosts"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: TheBasics/networkreachability.xml:16
msgid ""
"If you've ever work in tech support, you've undoubtably had users tell you "
"\"the Internet is down\". As a techie, you're pretty sure that no one pulled "
"the power cord from the Internet. Something must be going wrong somewhere "
"between the user's chair and the Internet."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: TheBasics/networkreachability.xml:21
msgid ""
"Assuming its a technical problem, you begin to search for the problem. "
"Perhaps the user's computer is turned off, maybe their network cable is "
"unplugged, or perhaps your organization's core router just took a dive. "
"Whatever the problem might be, one thing is most certain - the Internet "
"isn't down. It just happens to be unreachable for that user."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: TheBasics/networkreachability.xml:28
msgid ""
"Nagios is able to determine whether the hosts you're monitoring are in a "
"DOWN or UNREACHABLE state. These are very different (although related) "
"states and can help you quickly determine the root cause of network "
"problems. Here's how the reachability logic works to distinguish between "
"these two states..."
msgstr ""

